<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 13 at 8:05AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern McIntosh
and northwestern Pittsburg Counties through 845 AM CDT...
At 805 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from near Hanna to 3 miles northwest of Stuart.
Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Crowder...                        Canadian...
Indianola...                      Ashland...
Haywood...                        Scipio...
Arpelar...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
